             applicable Telegram guidelines, as amended from time to time;

       (ii)  The Licensor bears no responsibility for any suspension, ban,
             termination, or other enforcement action taken by Telegram
             against Your account, bot, or user base as a result of Your
             use of the Work;

       (iii) If Your use of the Work results in any abuse of the Telegram
             platform — including but not limited to spam, unauthorized
             mass messaging via the broadcast subsystem of the Work,
             scraping user data, circumventing rate limits (the cooldown
             middleware of the Work is a best-effort safeguard, not a
             guarantee), violating user privacy, or any other activity
             that Telegram prohibits — You are solely liable for all
             consequences, legal or otherwise, arising from such abuse;

       (iv)  You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the
             Licensor and all Contributors from any claims, damages,
             fines, or losses asserted by Telegram, its affiliates, or
             third parties as a result of Your non-compliant or abusive
             use of the Work;

       (v)   The Licensor reserves the right to immediately terminate
             Your license under Section 9 upon credible evidence of Your
             use of the Work in violation of Telegram's Terms of Service
             or applicable law.

    c. AI-PROVIDER COMPLIANCE.

       The Work ships with an opt-in AI layer (see the ``FEATURE_AI_*``
       flags and ``xtv_support.infrastructure.ai``) that, when enabled,
       transmits message content, ticket history, and/or media to
       third-party AI Providers selected by You. You acknowledge and
       agree that:

       (i)   You are solely responsible for reading, accepting, and
             complying with the terms of service, acceptable-use policies,
             data-processing agreements, and any other legal terms of
             every AI Provider You configure for the Work (including but
             not limited to Anthropic, OpenAI, Google Gemini, and any
             local or self-hosted inference endpoint);

       (ii)  The Licensor makes no representation or warranty about the
             behaviour, accuracy, safety, cost, availability, or privacy
             practices of any AI Provider and bears no responsibility for
             outputs produced by those Providers, including but not
             limited to hallucinated content, harmful content, copyright
             violations, or PII leakage;

       (iii) Any AI-Provider costs (token fees, subscription fees, rate-
             limit upgrades) incurred while the Work is running are
             entirely Your responsibility, regardless of whether such
             costs result from Your intended use, misuse, a runaway loop,
             or a bug in the Work;

       (iv)  If You disable the PII-redaction safeguard
             (``AI_PII_REDACTION=false``), You explicitly assume all
             liability for any personal data transmitted to AI Providers
             as a result, including but not limited to any consequences
             under applicable data-protection law;

       (v)   You are responsible for informing Your end users, where
             legally required, that AI-based processing is taking place
             on their messages, and for obtaining any consent required
             under applicable law.

    d. END-USER DATA AND DATA PROTECTION RESPONSIBILITY.

       The Work stores and processes End-User Data in its MongoDB
       collections (including but not limited to ``tickets``, ``users``,
       ``csat_responses``, ``audit_log``, ``ai_usage``, ``kb_articles``,
       ``macros``) and, when enabled, transmits portions of it to AI
       Providers (Section 12(c)) and to outbound bridges (Discord,
       Slack, webhooks). You acknowledge and agree that:

       (i)   For any Hosted instance of the Work, You are the data
             controller (or equivalent role under applicable law) with
             respect to all End-User Data stored by that instance. The
             Licensor is not a data controller, data processor, or
             sub-processor for Your Hosted instance;

       (ii)  You are solely responsible for complying with every
             applicable data-protection regime, including but not limited
             to the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the
             UK GDPR, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), the
             Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP), the Brazilian
             LGPD, and any sector-specific rules (HIPAA, PCI-DSS, …) that
             apply to Your user base;

       (iii) The Work ships GDPR-adjacent tooling (``/gdpr export``,
             ``/gdpr delete`` with a 30-day soft-delete grace period, TTL
             retention on audit logs) as a convenience, NOT as a
             certified compliance product. You must verify that the
             tooling meets Your specific legal obligations before relying
             on it, and You must extend it where Your jurisdiction
             requires stricter behaviour;

       (iv)  Any breach of security, data loss, unauthorised access, or
             unlawful disclosure of End-User Data from Your Hosted
             instance is Your responsibility — including any notification
             obligations to affected users and to supervisory
             authorities. The Licensor shall not be liable for any such
             breach regardless of its cause;

       (v)   You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the
             Licensor and all Contributors from any claims, damages,
             fines, or losses asserted by end users, regulators, or
